The <b>Cinnamon Hummingbird</b> (<i>Amazilia rutila</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hummingbird" title="Hummingbird">hummingbird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trochilidae" title="Trochilidae" class="mw-redirect">Trochilidae</a> family. It is found from northwestern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a> to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica" title="Costa Rica">Costa Rica</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a>, subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests, subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shrubland" title="Shrubland">shrubland</a>, and heavily degraded former forest.
